programme.title: Frantic
programme.desc: In a hotel room in Paris, a doctor comes out of the shower and finds that his wife has disappeared. He soon finds himself caught up in a world of intrigue, espionage, gangsters, drugs and murder.

programme.title: Legends of the Fall
programme.desc: An epic tale, set in the Rocky Mountains of Montana in the early 1900s, of three brothers and their father living in the remote wilderness and how their lives are affected by love, betrayal and brotherhood. After being discharged, Colonel Ludlow decides to raise his three sons in the wilds of Montana, where they can grow up away from the government and society he has learned to despise. As the brothers set out to fight a war in Europe, suspicion and jealousy threatens to tear apart their once indestructible bond when Susanna enters their lives.

programme.title: Last Action Hero
programme.desc: A projectionist allows 11-year-old boy Danny to a private midnight preview of the latest movie featuring his idol and superhero, Jack Slater. A magic ticket transports the boy into the film, where he helps his hero chase the baddie, who in turn breaks through the screen to wreak havoc in real-life, with the help of an evil sidekick.

programme.title: Innerspace
programme.desc: A test pilot is miniaturised in a secret experiment, and accidentally injected into a hapless store clerk.

programme.title: E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial
programme.desc: While visiting the Earth at Night, a group of alien botanists is discovered and disturbed by an approaching human task force. Because of the more than hasty take-off, one of the visitors is left behind. The little alien finds himself all alone on a very strange planet. Fortunately, the extra-terrestrial soon finds a friend and emotional companion in 10-year-old Elliot, who discovered him looking for food in his familys garden shed. While E.T. slowly gets acquainted with Elliots brother Michael, his sister Gertie as well as with Earth customs, members of the task force work day and night to track down the whereabouts of Earths first visitor from Outer Space.

programme.title: Close Encounters of the Third Kind
programme.desc: Power company repairman Roy Neary witnesses unidentified flying objects in the skies near his Muncie, Indiana home. The encounter sets into action a startling chain of dramatic events. Trying desperately to understand what he has seen, Neary is increasingly driven to the emotional edge by the governmental cover up thats blocking him. With his wife struggling in vain to understand what is happening as their relationship disintegrates, Neary finds an ally in Jillian Guiler, a woman who has also witnessed nocturnal encounters and whose young son has been abducted by the alien visitors. As Roy and Jillian look for an answer to the extraordinary mystery that has engulfed them, an international team of scientists led by Claude Lacombe, a dedicated French expert on extraordinary phenomena, also pursues the truth. As Lacombe and company seek to understand the phenomenon of the skies and look for a communications break-through, their cosmic detective work reaches from the Indiana plains across the world to a remote hillside in India and then to the one place that holds the answer in an ultimate close encounter.

programme.desc: For the third time, Detroit cop Axel Foley returns to Beverly Hills, this time to track down bad guys at an amusement park. Judge Reinhold and Bronson Pinchot are also back for this third instalment.

programme.title: Waynes World
programme.desc: From Waynes basement, Wayne and Garth broadcast a talk-show called "Waynes World" on local public access television. The show comes to the attention of a sleazy network executive who wants to produce a big-budget version of "Waynes World"-and he also wants Waynes girlfriend, a rock singer named Cassandra. Wayne and Garth have to battle the executive not only to save their show, but also Cassandra.

programme.title: The Nutty Professor
programme.desc: Dr Sherman Klump, a kind, calorically challenged genetics professor who longs to shed his 400-pound frame in order to win the heart of the beautiful Carla Purty. So, with one swig of his experimental fat-reducing serum, Sherman becomes Buddy Love, a fast-talking, pumped up, plumped-down Don Juan. Can Sherman stop his buff alter ego before its too late, or will Buddy have the last laugh?

programme.title: Jaws

programme.title: Close Encounters of the Third Kind
programme.desc: Power company repairman Roy Neary witnesses unidentified flying objects in the skies near his Muncie, Indiana home. The encounter sets into action a startling chain of dramatic events. Trying desperately to understand what he has seen, Neary is increasingly driven to the emotional edge by the governmental cover up thats blocking him. With his wife struggling in vain to understand what is happening as their relationship disintegrates, Neary finds an ally in Jillian Guiler, a woman who has also witnessed nocturnal encounters and whose young son has been abducted by the alien visitors. As Roy and Jillian look for an answer to the extraordinary mystery that has engulfed them, an international team of scientists led by Claude Lacombe, a dedicated French expert on extraordinary phenomena, also pursues the truth. As Lacombe and company seek to understand the phenomenon of the skies and look for a communications break-through, their cosmic detective work reaches from the Indiana plains across the world to a remote hillside in India and then to the one place that holds the answer in an ultimate close encounter.

programme.title: Bloodline Detectives
programme.sub-title: Stephanie Isaacson - Schoolbag In The Road
programme.desc: In Las Vegas, Nevada, on June 1st, 1989, Stephanie Isaacson sets off on her morning walk to school. She never makes it. That same evening, her familys worst fears are confirmed.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: In Modesto, California, a young mother is brutally murdered in her home. Police find Debi Whitlocks nearly decapitated body lying in the hallway. There is blood on the walls. Her nightgown is pulled over her face and a knife lays between her legs. Even worse, her three-year-old daughter is sleeping just feet away. Except for her purse, nothing in the house is missing or out of place. Could she have known her killer? As the investigation unfolds, police zero in on two suspects - her husband who she had recently reconciled with, and her boyfriend. But with little evidence, the case goes cold for everyone - except Debi Whitlocks mother. She refuses to give up and for six years she keeps her daughters case alive in the media. The question is, can a mothers love help to track down a killer?

programme.title: Murder at My Door
programme.desc: When a nurse dies after ingesting a sedative, a fellow medical professional comes under question; a horrifying truth is revealed.

programme.title: The Real Manhunter
programme.desc: Following ex-detective Colin Sutton, a former senior investigating officer with the Metropolitan Police, as he looks back at his most important cases and the investigations that solved them.

programme.title: When Missing Turns to Murder
programme.desc: British true crime documentary series using powerful and emotional testimony from families and friends when a missing persons enquiry turns into a murder investigation.

programme.title: The First 48
programme.desc: In Miami, Florida, Detective Freddy Ponce and Sgt Louis Melancon unravel the mystery of a man found shot dead in his car. The key to the case could be the victims cell phone, which was stolen shortly after the murder. In Memphis, Tennessee, Sgts Caroline Mason, Tony Mullins and JT Max investigate the murder of a man found shot dead in a backyard. After they capture the man they believe is their suspect, the case takes an unexpected turn.

programme.title: Bloodline Detectives
programme.sub-title: Tonya McKinley - Her Last New Years Eve
programme.desc: In 1985, in Pensacola, Florida, on New Years Day, the body of Tonya McKinley is found lying on the side of a city street. Shes found partially naked and has been sexually assaulted.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: While on their way to a Boston maternity class, a white suburban couple is carjacked and shot in a violent inner-city neighbourhood. On the verge of death, the man calls 911, and when police arrive on the scene, he describes their assailant as an African-American male in a jogging suit. The victims are taken to hospital, and while the man, Chuck Stuart, survives, his wife Carol and their unborn child do not. Exacerbating racial tensions in the city, the case generates huge media interest and investigators are under enormous pressure to find the culprit. No physical evidence is found in the car, but when police establish a hotline, hundreds of calls come in, and two possible suspects emerge. Did the crime stem from a drug deal gone wrong? Or could there be a third suspect and a much darker motive for murder?

programme.title: Cops Reloaded
programme.desc: Cops Reloaded revisits some of the most memorable suspects, car chases and action-packed moments from televisions popular reality program.

programme.title: Cops
programme.desc: Television cameras follow real-life law enforcement officers and capture the action as they perform their daily duty to serve and protect the public.

programme.title: Murdered at First Sight
programme.desc: Most killers know their victims, Murdered At First Sight investigates the alarming rise in "Stranger Murders" and the challenges faced by the police in tracking down the suspect of an entirely random homicide.

programme.title: BTK: A Killer Among Us
programme.desc: The terrible legacy of Dennis Rader, better known as the BTK Killer for Bind, Torture, Kill, spanned three decades before he was finally captured and incarcerated. Take an in depth look at the entirety of the murderous carnage he unleashed.

programme.title: Homicide With Ron Iddles
programme.desc: One of Australias greatest detectives reveals the untold stories of his most challenging cases. This series takes you behind the news headlines, on a minute-by-minute journey with Ron Iddles.

programme.title: Crimes That Shook Britain
programme.desc: In 1992, 25-year-old Stephanie Slater was abducted from an empty house and held for eight torturous days in a make shift coffin. Her captor was a crazed one legged man, Michael Sams. His intention was to hold her for ransom. Stephanie endured painful days and nights in the back of his grubby workshop. She was raped, tortured and made to lie in a bin for up to 23 hours a day. Her ordeal finally came to a head when Sams carried out his elaborate plot and received 175,000 pounds ransom. Police eventually tracked him down and brought him to justice. Some of the money has never been recovered. Stephanies terrifying account is told in gripping detail in this film. Her ordeal went down in history as the first ransom demand in the UK where the hostage was released.

programme.title: I Survived a Crime
programme.desc: A woman is trapped in the backseat of her car after a man steals her vehicle and leads police on a wild chase. A mans neighbor is forced to intervene after an arsonist attempts to burn his home down. A woman bites her rideshare driver; and more.

programme.title: Forensic Files
programme.desc: It takes a long time and a very hot fire to cremate a human body and thus destroy any evidence of foul play. But the medical examiner who performed the autopsy on the badly burnt body of Charles Jack Lynch found telltale clues; not only had the victim been burned, hed also been stabbed - 24 times, with two different knives. Police knew that a person acting alone would probably use only one weapon, so investigators searched for a couple of killers.

programme.title: Forensic Files
programme.desc: The victim had ingested a massive amount of cyanide. An unlikely clue - a flaw on a mailing envelope - exposed a murderer who was willing to kill innocent people to get the one person he wanted.

programme.title: Forensic Files
programme.desc: The body of a 16-year-old girl was discovered nine months after she disappeared. Forensic scientists found clues that painted a virtual portrait of her killer. They knew he had a dog, he worked for the postal service, and that he had red carpeting in his home. Now all they had to do was find him.

Except for her purse, nothing in the house is missing or out of place. Could she have known her killer? As the investigation unfolds, police zero in on two suspects - her husband who she had recently reconciled with, and her boyfriend. But with little evidence, the case goes cold for everyone - except Debi Whitlocks mother. She refuses to give up and for six years she keeps her daughters case alive in the media. The question is, can a mothers love help to track down a killer?

Some of the money has never been recovered. Stephanies terrifying account is told in gripping detail in this film. Her ordeal went down in history as the first ransom demand in the UK where the hostage was released.

programme.desc: In Miami, a mechanic is shot to death in his shop. Detective Juan Hererra and his team focus on the victims everyday habits to find a reason why someone would want him dead. In Dallas a young, small-town farmer is murdered while trying to buy a used car. With only a nickname to go on, Detective John Palmer and his team need to track down the cars seller to help them find their suspect.

programme.title: Power and Glory of The Habsburgs
programme.desc: This series traces the historical sites tied to the illustrious House of Habsburg-Lorraine, offering a fresh perspective on an 800-year legacy that shaped Europes history.

programme.title: Royals, British Aristocracy and the Nazis
programme.desc: The British royal family has always been a symbol of Nazi resistance. However, time and again, information from different sources has surfaced about the Windsors secret sympathy for the Nazi regime. The newest finds have even fuelled the suspicion that, in the summer of 1940, the abdicated King Edward VIII may have leaked sensitive war-related information to Hitlers regime with the hopes of securing their support for his plans to re assume the throne.

programme.title: History Uncovered
programme.sub-title: Sub-Primes: Blame it on the USA?
programme.desc: The subprime crisis has gone down in history as an American disaster. And yet. The shock wave hit the Old Continent hard. By revealing the fault lines in the Eurozone, it triggered the worst recession in its history and jeopardized its fragile union. At the end of the day, although the United States got back on the path to growth fairly quickly, Europe is still picking up the pieces today.

programme.title: Line of Fire
programme.desc: The story of the Universal Ruler - the man who succeeded his chieftain father at age 13 and had to struggle to overcome hostile tribes. Who then could have predicted the glories to come? His military victories included the conquest of China and other empires stretching from the Black Sea to the pacific. A remarkable administrator and ruler, Genghis Khans system of khanites- the means by which he ruled conquered lands - lasted for more than 400 years after his death.

programme.title: Dogfights
programme.desc: The Israeli air force mastered the use of the Mirage III over decades of intense air combat with its neighbours. Go into battle with Israels ace of aces, Giora Epstein, as he takes on a swarm of Egyptian MiG-21s in one of the most thrilling dogfights of the jet age. State-of-the-art computer graphics are used to recreate famous battles. First-hand accounts, rare archival footage and original shooting will make the viewer feel like theyre in the battle facing the enemy.

programme.desc: The citizens of Japan could not believe their eyes when the Americans dared to fly an audacious endurance mission over Tokyo only a few months after Pearl Harbour.

programme.title: WWII: Witness To War
programme.desc: By early 1945, the end was in sight. But now Nazi occupied Eastern Europe was giving up its secrets to horrified Allied troops. As they advanced they discovered the nightmare of the concentration camps, where piles of bodies and skeletal people bore testimony to the sheer scale of the Holocaust, the evils of which were almost too much for ordinary soldiers to comprehend. Survivors remember in this episode. By the end of April the Red Army was in Berlin and Hitler was deep in his bunker. He and his new wife Eva Braun committed suicide on April 30th. Just one week later - May 7 - the formal unconditional German surrender came. The following day was declared VE Day in Britain and the "German War" was over. But Japan still fought on.

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: In one of WWIIs most daring raids, Captain Otto Skorzeny, leader of Germanys special forces, led a glider assault against a remote mountaintop hotel outside Rome on September 12, 1943. His mission: rescue the imprisoned Italian dictator Benito Mussolini. A surprise attack overwhelmed the guards, and after a precarious flight off the mountain, Il Duce reunited with his Axis partner, Adolf Hitler. This, and other Skorzeny exploits, led to him being called the most dangerous man in Europe.

programme.title: Dogfights
programme.desc: Watch as A-1H Skyraider pilots pit their prop-driven workhorses against a lethal jet-powered MiG-17.

programme.title: Secrets of World War II
programme.desc: Amazing new footage has just become available which shows the raid by the US air force against the Ploesti oil fields in Romania, which supplied 60 percent of Hitlers oil in 1943.

programme.title: History of Warfare
programme.desc: The Battle of Borodino took place during the Emperor Napoleons disastrous Russian invasion of 1812 and was one of the most crucial battles of the entire Napoleonic era. The two sides met just 95km from Moscow, on September 7, 1812. For a man who had earned a reputation as a military genius, Napoleon failed to make the most of his long-awaited opportunity. He simply hurled his troops at the determined Russians. The result was the single biggest bloodbath of the Napoleonic wars - more than 68,000 troops were killed or wounded.

programme.title: Countdown to Surrender: Last 100 Days
programme.desc: The final act of the Second World War is its most costly episode. More than one million German soldiers die in 1945 alone. The last three months of dictatorship and war bring fanaticism and flight, murder and civil courage, delusion, struggle and collapse. The last rebellion of the murderous regime.

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: As dawn broke on August 19, 1942, 2nd Canadian Infantry Division troops, supported by British Commandos and US Rangers, launched a major raid on the German-held French port of Dieppe. Though only a fraction of the men made it back to England, the lessons learned there were put to good use on D-Day.

programme.title: Countdown to Surrender: Last 100 Days
programme.desc: The final act of the Second World War is its most costly episode. More than one million German soldiers die in 1945 alone. Before peace comes in May, liberators and the liberated alike must suffer the unimaginable. The last three months of dictatorship and war bring fanaticism and flight, murder and civil courage, delusion, struggle and collapse. The last rebellion of the murderous regime.

programme.title: Secrets in the Ice
programme.desc: Mountain climbers in California find the body of a U.S. Army soldier. In Alaska, strange bundles of canvas and wood high up on a mountain are discovered. Volcanic glass is found in an unexpected place. A vital WWII weather station is uncovered.

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: In one of WWIIs most daring raids, Captain Otto Skorzeny, leader of Germanys special forces, led a glider assault against a remote mountaintop hotel outside Rome on September 12, 1943. His mission: rescue the imprisoned Italian dictator Benito Mussolini. A surprise attack overwhelmed the guards, and after a precarious flight off the mountain, Il Duce reunited with his Axis partner, Adolf Hitler. This, and other Skorzeny exploits, led to him being called the most dangerous man in Europe.

programme.title: Secrets of World War II

programme.title: History of Warfare
programme.desc: The Battle of Borodino took place during the Emperor Napoleons disastrous Russian invasion of 1812 and was one of the most crucial battles of the entire Napoleonic era. The two sides met just 95km from Moscow, on September 7, 1812. For a man who had earned a reputation as a military genius, Napoleon failed to make the most of his long-awaited opportunity. He simply hurled his troops at the determined Russians. The result was the single biggest bloodbath of the Napoleonic wars - more than 68,000 troops were killed or wounded.

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: As dawn broke on August 19, 1942, 2nd Canadian Infantry Division troops, supported by British Commandos and US Rangers, launched a major raid on the German-held French port of Dieppe.
